    <!-- Terms & Privacy -->
    <string name="terms_title">Terms &amp; Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="terms_subtitle">No legal jargon, just honest answers about your data.</string>
    <string name="terms_updated">Last updated: June 2026</string>
    <string name="terms_s1_title">A personal project, openly shared</string>
    <string name="terms_s1_body">Chronos started as a bot I built for myself. I became happy enough with it to share it — and that\'s the whole story. There\'s no company behind this, no investors, no business plan. It\'s a side project maintained by one person in their free time.</string>
    <string name="terms_s2_title">What data is collected</string>
    <string name="terms_s2_body">When you create an account, the following is stored: your email address (used for verification and password reset only), your username, your password (bcrypt-hashed — nobody can read it), your timezone, your Discord identity if you connect via OAuth, and the content of your reminders.</string>
    <string name="terms_s3_title">Your password is safe — even from me</string>
    <string name="terms_s3_body">Passwords are hashed with bcrypt before storage. There is no technical way to retrieve your password. If you forget it, only a password reset can help.</string>
    <string name="terms_s4_title">How your data is used</string>
    <string name="terms_s4_body">Your data is never shared with any third party, never sold, and never used for advertising. Email and reminder content may be visible to the developer for debugging purposes only.</string>
    <string name="terms_s5_title">No monetization — ever on your data</string>
    <string name="terms_s5_body">There is zero intention to monetize Chronos while it stays within reasonable scope. User data would never be part of any equation, in any scenario.</string>
    <string name="terms_s6_title">Service availability</string>
    <string name="terms_s6_body">Chronos runs on a personal server in France. No uptime guarantee can be offered. You can check the current status at chronosrmd.com/status.</string>
    <string name="terms_s7_title">Your rights &amp; account deletion</string>
    <string name="terms_s7_body">You can delete your account at any time from the Account page. Deletion permanently removes all associated data: profile, reminders, and destinations. There is no archive or grace period.</string>
    <string name="terms_s8_title">Self-hosting</string>
    <string name="terms_s8_body">Chronos is open-source under the MIT License. If you prefer to control your own data, you can self-host the full stack. In that case, this policy does not apply — you are the operator.</string>
    <string name="terms_s9_title">Questions?</string>
    <string name="terms_s9_body">For any questions or data requests, reach out via the contact form at chronosrmd.com/contact or on the Discord server.</string>

